chrome_devtools_inspected_window

Top-Level Variables
devtools_inspected_window: ChromeDevtoolsInspectedWindow
Classes
ChromeDevtoolsInspectedWindow

Use the chrome.devtools.inspectedWindow API to interact with the inspected window: obtain the tab ID for the inspected page, evaluate the code in the context of the inspected window, reload the page, or obtain the list of resources within the page.

Top-Level Variables

static final ChromeDevtoolsInspectedWindow devtools_inspected_window

Fields

final Stream onResourceAdded
final Stream onResourceContentCommitted
final dynamic tabId

Getters and Setters

Stream<dynamic> get onResourceAdded

Fired when a new resource is added to the inspected page.

Stream<dynamic> get onResourceContentCommitted

Fired when a new revision of the resource is committed (e.g. user saves an edited version of the resource in the Developer Tools).

dynamic get tabId

The ID of the tab being inspected. This ID may be used with chrome.tabs.* API.

Methods

void eval(String expression, dynamic callback)

Evaluates a JavaScript expression in the context of the main frame of the inspected page. The expression must evaluate to a JSON-compliant object, otherwise an exception is thrown. expression An expression to evaluate. callback A function called when evaluation completes.

void getResources(dynamic callback)

Retrieves the list of resources from the inspected page. callback A function that receives the list of resources when the request completes.

void reload(dynamic reloadOptions)

Reloads the inspected page.
